WEBVTT

00:00.578 --> 00:06.524
How many of you know what is coming up on Thursday?

00:08.466 --> 00:09.387
There's a book study.

00:09.747 --> 00:17.115
Now here's what a book study is, is we gather together, it goes from 6 a.m. on Thursday morning to 7 a.m.

00:17.135 --> 00:19.297
Always finished on time, okay?

00:19.577 --> 00:21.799
Because we know you got to go to work, other places like that.

00:22.460 --> 00:23.561
So we always finish on time.

00:24.041 --> 00:28.626
We're using John Maxwell's book, and of course, you know, Maxwell gets paid

00:28.834 --> 00:33.601
you know, normally somewhere between 50 and $100,000 to speak for 45 minutes.

00:33.641 --> 00:37.826
So we're leveraging his experience and knowledge.

00:37.886 --> 00:54.489
What we do is read through a few chapters of the book each week and then I'll introduce the topic and we sit around tables and you sit around tables with folks who have been where you've been or are where you are so we can discuss and learn from each other.

00:54.529 --> 00:58.034
It's a really powerful opportunity to grow

00:58.210 --> 01:02.475
and mature, and it's happening Thursday at 6 a.m. Now, how many of you are planning on being there?

01:04.698 --> 01:07.341
All right, 10.

01:07.361 --> 01:09.163
Now, I want to challenge you on this, okay?

01:09.584 --> 01:12.948
I want to challenge you because when I see that, here's what comes into my mind.

01:13.508 --> 01:28.146
My assumption, then, is the vast majority of you, 90% of you, then, are very, very happy with where you're at in life, content, in the sense of your marriage is awesome, you got all the money you need, you love where you're at in your profession,

01:28.322 --> 01:32.148
Your kids are awesome, your college degree, your grades are great.

01:32.469 --> 01:38.458
In other words, that's the only reason I could understand, and even then, as I'll challenge you, why you wouldn't be a part of this.

01:39.420 --> 01:44.308
Because see, if you study success, you know what, you realize it doesn't fall out of the sky on people.

01:45.310 --> 01:53.042
If you talk to people who are driving the cars you wish you were driving, the reason they're driving those cars is because somewhere along the line, they paid a price.

01:53.922 --> 02:00.453
They decided that they were going to do what others were unwilling to do so they could experience what most people don't experience.

02:01.314 --> 02:04.419
If you talk to people who have a great marriage, it didn't just happen.

02:05.261 --> 02:06.062
They work at that.

02:06.142 --> 02:07.043
They grow.

02:07.124 --> 02:09.187
They've read certain books.

02:09.307 --> 02:11.190
They went to certain conferences.

02:11.250 --> 02:13.554
They've paid certain prices.

02:14.690 --> 02:16.594
See, success has a cost.

02:16.614 --> 02:17.556
It has a price tag.

02:17.776 --> 02:19.199
And can I tell you something about success?

02:19.279 --> 02:20.401
It never goes on sale.

02:20.702 --> 02:22.726
Success doesn't show up at 10 AM.

02:22.766 --> 02:23.908
It shows up at 6 AM.

02:25.551 --> 02:29.319
That's why most people don't exceed, because they're unwilling to pay the price for success.

02:29.539 --> 02:30.762
So I want to challenge you in that.

02:31.663 --> 02:35.090
I want to challenge you to come and be a part of something that's unique.

02:35.682 --> 02:38.945
It's unique in that we get the opportunity to learn from John Maxwell.

02:39.426 --> 02:51.999
I get the opportunity to introduce a topic and then you get the opportunity to learn from people who are further ahead, who have experienced certain things in life that maybe you're experiencing, to learn from one another.

02:52.300 --> 02:54.362
But then I want to challenge even a little further.

02:54.442 --> 02:56.764
If you're here and you say, yeah, you know, I have succeeded.

02:57.305 --> 03:01.970
Well, why in the world would you not come and give that to others?

03:03.426 --> 03:11.479
See, there's a point in life when you move beyond success because success is about what's happening in your life to significance.

03:11.519 --> 03:13.923
That's when you start to give, not just receive.

03:14.905 --> 03:16.788
You start to teach, not just learn.

03:17.690 --> 03:23.119
So I'll be honest, I cannot understand why in the world if you call yourself a Christ follower, right?

03:23.179 --> 03:27.666
You love God, why in the world you would hang on in your bed.

03:28.770 --> 03:38.505
to what God's blessed you with when there are people willing to get up early and come just to experience the wisdom and knowledge that you've had in your life.

03:39.026 --> 03:39.987
I challenge you to be here.

03:41.169 --> 03:46.938
People need to hear because they're gonna learn not from Maxwell even though he's great or his book or something I say.

03:46.998 --> 03:50.965
It's something that God's done in your life that's gonna forever change and challenge their life.

03:52.187 --> 03:53.288
So it's easier to sleep in.

03:53.328 --> 03:54.450
I understand that.

03:54.722 --> 03:59.668
I understand you're reading a million books and you've been to a million, but this is an opportunity.

03:59.688 --> 04:04.473
We don't do it very often once, sometimes twice a year as often as we do it.

04:04.813 --> 04:05.594
How many weeks is it?

04:06.435 --> 04:07.256
It's four weeks.

04:08.518 --> 04:13.643
It's not a very big commitment, but it could have an incredibly big and large impact on your life.

04:14.024 --> 04:17.888
So much so that maybe the thing you've been praying for is going to sit at the table right beside you.

04:19.570 --> 04:21.532
And for a few hours of sleep, you're going to miss that.

04:22.273 --> 04:23.154
I just wouldn't do that.

04:24.098 --> 04:25.940
So I just challenge you on that.

04:26.000 --> 04:29.384
Don't miss this opportunity to come and be a part of something.

04:29.404 --> 04:31.366
And we're going to be doing it at all of our campuses.

04:31.726 --> 04:36.111
Very, very excited about it because these kind of things have had incredible impacts in my life.

04:36.931 --> 04:39.934
We just got back from a conference that I did not want to go to.

04:41.977 --> 04:43.158
Just another place to go.

04:43.178 --> 04:45.901
And the only reason I went is for two reasons.

04:46.181 --> 04:51.026
One to learn and two to pour into others from our team.

04:51.490 --> 04:53.092
So I just challenge you to do that.

04:53.412 --> 04:55.295
Hey, pull out the outline you got when you came in.

04:55.355 --> 04:59.840
And I want, this is what this hope is gonna be about.

05:00.180 --> 05:01.822
We're gonna talk about panic.

05:01.842 --> 05:03.404
We're gonna talk about fear.

05:04.406 --> 05:08.170
Because anxiety, worry, our world is crazy.

05:08.571 --> 05:10.273
And so there's a lot going on out there.

05:10.353 --> 05:13.296
But then in our own world, there's a lot of crazy stuff happening, right?

05:13.797 --> 05:15.859
There's lots of things to be afraid of.

05:15.919 --> 05:17.121
Now here is the thing.

05:17.581 --> 05:18.162
Fear.

05:18.946 --> 05:21.751
Always wears a mask.

05:22.573 --> 05:26.300
You wouldn't believe how hard it is to find a Halloween mask in the month of August.

05:28.284 --> 05:31.450
Amber had to drive all the way to Miami to get this mask, okay?

05:31.810 --> 05:33.213
But it's a pretty scary one.

05:34.375 --> 05:36.860
And fear always wears a mask when it shows up.

05:37.120 --> 05:38.122
And here's what I mean by it.

05:38.463 --> 05:41.468
In fear shows up, we ask certain questions.

05:41.529 --> 05:42.290
What is it?

05:43.746 --> 05:45.850
I mean, what does it mean?

05:45.990 --> 05:48.154
What does cancer mean?

05:48.274 --> 05:50.238
What does old age mean?

05:50.358 --> 05:53.323
What does a North Korean dictator mean, right?

05:53.544 --> 05:54.626
He is wearing a mask.

05:54.686 --> 05:55.387
Who is it?

05:55.648 --> 05:56.709
What are they going to do?

05:56.730 --> 06:00.697
And is it going to hurt?

06:02.179 --> 06:03.121
And when are they going to do it?

06:04.724 --> 06:08.050
Fear always wears a mask.

06:08.706 --> 06:10.248
I put in my notes.

06:10.308 --> 06:11.509
We're asking the question, what is it?

06:11.849 --> 06:12.610
What is it going to do?

06:12.770 --> 06:13.731
And when is it going to happen?

06:13.751 --> 06:18.577
It's kind of like when we were coming back from the conference I mentioned, it was in Chicago, so we're flying back.

06:19.137 --> 06:24.603
And have you ever been on one of those flights where everybody's talking and they're pushing the car and they're selling the cokes?

06:24.663 --> 06:27.186
And then all of a sudden you're running the turbulence.

06:28.467 --> 06:31.170
And it's playing goes like this and everybody gets quiet.

06:32.311 --> 06:32.812
That's what happened.

06:32.832 --> 06:33.633
Everybody got quiet.

06:33.933 --> 06:38.418
And then the pilot, you know, he comes on the sound system and he's like,

06:38.594 --> 06:44.884
We ran into some turbulence, and we're going to ask all of our flight attendants to be seated.

06:45.765 --> 06:47.327
Well, that freaks you out a little bit more.

06:48.109 --> 06:52.175
Then he comes on, and he says, it looks like this turbulence is going to last for the length of the flight.

06:52.195 --> 06:52.916
I don't know why.

06:53.296 --> 06:54.979
Pilot's got a microphone, all right?

06:56.321 --> 06:57.703
I keep doing that, I don't know why.

06:57.884 --> 07:02.651
But anyways, he comes on and says, it's going to last the length of the flight, which is like two and a half hours.

07:04.213 --> 07:07.378
And they put away their carts, and they all sit down, and it's just quiet.

07:09.314 --> 07:10.455
Nobody's talking.

07:11.116 --> 07:11.476
Why?

07:11.797 --> 07:17.423
Well, because the moment you experience turbulence, you've got the monster, right?

07:17.463 --> 07:19.225
You're asking the question, what does that mean?

07:19.465 --> 07:20.346
What does turbulence mean?

07:20.366 --> 07:21.768
I mean, if you're not a pilot, do you know?

07:21.788 --> 07:26.393
I look out the window and I see a wing that looks really, really skinny that's flapping in the air.

07:27.414 --> 07:29.276
And then I see, have you ever looked at those engines?

07:29.777 --> 07:32.560
They're just like hanging on those wings.

07:32.580 --> 07:34.001
And I'm like, what's keeping that on there?

07:34.021 --> 07:38.386
This thing is keeping the plane in the air, but I don't know what's keeping it on the plane.

07:39.010 --> 07:44.218
I mean, my car seems to be stronger and it's falling apart all the time, right?

07:44.238 --> 07:45.380
It's like, what is it?

07:45.480 --> 07:48.385
And then you're asking the question, is it gonna hurt me?

07:48.525 --> 07:56.898
I read an article, 80%, you might need to know this, 80% of people who end up in a plane crash survive.

07:56.918 --> 08:01.265
80% of people who end up in a plane crash survive.

08:02.006 --> 08:04.690
Now, most of them die in the fire after, okay?

08:07.362 --> 08:09.326
And so you're asking the question, right?

08:09.446 --> 08:10.167
Am I going to live?

08:10.869 --> 08:13.514
Every time it goes down and back up, it's like, okay, is it going to crash?

08:13.554 --> 08:14.856
And if it crashes, am I going to live?

08:14.876 --> 08:16.379
And you're looking like, why do I wear flip flops?

08:16.419 --> 08:17.321
I know I shouldn't have wore them.

08:17.782 --> 08:21.168
You know?

08:21.289 --> 08:24.114
There's all of these questions.

08:24.706 --> 08:28.991
that create fear, they create worry, they create anxiety, and they lock us out.

08:29.091 --> 08:30.893
It locked us out of community.

08:31.133 --> 08:32.495
People are no longer talking.

08:32.775 --> 08:34.217
It locked us out of peace.

08:34.317 --> 08:37.400
Instead, people are worried and their stomach is tumbling.

08:38.241 --> 08:42.827
We can react to fear or worry or anxiety.

08:43.187 --> 08:45.710
Sometimes we can even overreact, can't we?

08:47.011 --> 08:47.912
Let me show you a picture.

08:47.932 --> 08:48.673
Do you know what this is?

08:50.636 --> 08:51.036
What is that?

08:52.257 --> 08:52.818
It's a frog.

08:53.826 --> 08:56.455
Not a special frog, it's just a frog.

08:57.097 --> 08:58.642
My middle son, Carson.

09:00.528 --> 09:07.090
I don't know if he's so much today, but up until the age of 18, for sure, and maybe even, he was scared of frogs.

09:07.810 --> 09:09.813
I don't mean just, ooh, I don't like frogs.

09:10.233 --> 09:17.482
In case you're watching in one of the other parts of the country, here in South Florida, at certain times of the year, we have more frogs than at other times of the year.

09:17.502 --> 09:18.123
You ever notice that?

09:18.444 --> 09:19.986
I don't know if that's because we have more bugs.

09:20.066 --> 09:21.848
I don't know what, but there are more frogs.

09:21.868 --> 09:27.635
And during those time of the year, we'd get ready as a family to go somewhere at night, and that's when the frogs tend to show up.

09:27.656 --> 09:32.121
And Carson would make me go out and see if there were any frogs before he'd walk to the car.

09:33.603 --> 09:35.826
And if there were any, I had to hide them.

09:36.322 --> 09:38.865
I had to get rid of him or he wouldn't go.

09:38.885 --> 09:40.207
I don't want to go.

09:40.788 --> 09:41.008
Why?

09:41.048 --> 09:41.749
Well, there's frogs.

09:43.932 --> 09:45.074
I don't know why.

09:45.114 --> 09:46.516
Irrational, right?

09:46.576 --> 09:49.320
There are some fears that are just irrational.

09:49.340 --> 09:52.284
We overreact to those things.

09:52.704 --> 09:54.347
And how do we react to fear?

09:54.387 --> 09:56.229
We tend to run and hide, don't we?

09:56.950 --> 09:58.652
We're calling this series panic room.

09:59.113 --> 10:00.435
That's where we run and hide.

10:01.436 --> 10:02.738
Let me show you a few pictures.

10:03.394 --> 10:05.456
Here's a picture of a panic room.

10:05.516 --> 10:07.198
Some of them are putting closets.

10:07.218 --> 10:11.383
This gentleman has one or selling them, and he has it behind a bookshelf.

10:12.544 --> 10:12.924
Secret.

10:12.984 --> 10:20.613
So when the monster comes, whatever the monster is or looks like, he and his family can run, open up the bookshelf, and they can hide behind it.

10:20.833 --> 10:23.696
Now, the only problem is, is when you're in your panic room, you're locked in.

10:23.776 --> 10:26.279
You can't go.

10:26.319 --> 10:27.200
You can't do.

10:27.300 --> 10:27.981
You can't be.

10:28.021 --> 10:29.362
You're no longer free.

10:30.050 --> 10:35.840
In your mind, you may feel somewhat safe, but your hope is, is that the monster's not stronger than the room.

10:37.002 --> 10:39.386
Well, today, we don't just make panic rooms.

10:39.466 --> 10:42.531
We make like panic houses, right?

10:42.572 --> 10:45.136
People go out to Arizona, some folks in Arkansas.

10:45.156 --> 10:45.717
Here's one.

10:45.877 --> 10:46.919
This is pretty impressive, isn't it?

10:47.480 --> 10:55.634
I mean, look, when the zombies come, he's even got a helicopter so he can escape and get to his zombie proof, whatever, shelter there.

10:56.258 --> 10:57.419
All kinds of rooms.

10:57.439 --> 10:58.621
Here's an inside of one.

10:58.801 --> 10:59.081
Look at that.

10:59.101 --> 11:00.343
It's nicer than our houses.

11:02.866 --> 11:03.327
What are those?

11:03.367 --> 11:06.250
They're there to try to take away the fear.

11:07.512 --> 11:09.714
They're there so that we don't have to feel anxious.

11:09.774 --> 11:17.904
But even should you go to one of those, you find yourself locked in, not with peace, but with a lack of freedom.

11:17.924 --> 11:25.874
So we can either respond by being paralyzed or rather than react, we can respond to fear in faith or hope.

11:26.050 --> 11:26.671
you might say.

11:27.933 --> 11:33.720
Paul told Timothy, he said, Timothy, God hasn't given you the spirit of fear, but of power.

11:34.682 --> 11:40.389
When I was in high school, we put on a little play, and the pastor, I guess, you know, he knew something.

11:40.730 --> 11:44.314
He gave me Psalm 27, 1 and 2 to memorize.

11:45.276 --> 11:49.061
And I'll be honest with you, fear, anxiety, those are things I've wrestled with.

11:49.141 --> 11:50.002
I woke up

11:50.594 --> 11:54.262
Oh, it's been years ago now, but I was probably in my late 20s, early 30s.

11:54.603 --> 11:56.187
I just woke up one day and I was anxious.

11:56.347 --> 11:57.028
I didn't know why.

11:57.048 --> 11:59.474
I didn't know where it came from.

11:59.534 --> 12:03.082
It wasn't one of one specific thing, but it wouldn't go away.

12:04.646 --> 12:05.748
It didn't just last a day.

12:05.828 --> 12:06.830
It lasted months.

12:07.412 --> 12:08.434
Couldn't sleep the night.

12:10.274 --> 12:19.547
Just felt worried all the time, worried I was going to not outlive, you know, live to see my kids grow up and worried just about everything.

12:19.587 --> 12:23.072
Horrible, horrible experience.

12:24.093 --> 12:28.799
But this scripture has helped me and I think that it can help all of us, Psalm 27 one.

12:29.040 --> 12:30.001
Let's look at what it says.

12:30.041 --> 12:33.786
The Lord is my light and my salvation.

12:35.068 --> 12:36.850
Let's read this last part out loud together.

12:36.870 --> 12:37.331
You ready?

12:37.371 --> 12:39.474
So why?

12:41.282 --> 12:42.744
Let's do it a little better than that.

12:43.345 --> 12:44.346
So why?

12:44.366 --> 12:44.467
Yeah.

12:47.571 --> 12:48.933
The Lord is my light and my salvation.

12:49.013 --> 12:51.597
Therefore, why should I be afraid?

12:51.637 --> 12:56.945
So the fact that God is light and salvation ought to in some way impact our anxiety.

12:57.626 --> 13:00.490
Let's look at verse two, or the continuation of verse one.

13:00.831 --> 13:04.676
The Lord is my fortress protecting me from danger.

13:04.736 --> 13:06.939
So let's read this last part out loud together.

13:07.540 --> 13:08.722
So why?

13:09.954 --> 13:10.575
One more time.

13:10.815 --> 13:11.717
So why?

13:11.737 --> 13:14.401
Yeah, it goes on.

13:15.403 --> 13:20.992
When evil people come to devour me, when my enemies suppose, attack me, they will stumble and fall.

13:21.673 --> 13:26.380
Verse three, I love this, though a mighty army surrounds me, my heart will not be afraid.

13:26.721 --> 13:27.061
Why?

13:27.101 --> 13:30.607
Even if I am attacked, I will remain confident.

13:30.928 --> 13:34.994
So even the Bible doesn't say there's not monsters, don't be afraid.

13:35.938 --> 13:45.971
Scripture says there are monsters, but even when monsters appear, I can be confident because the Lord is my light, my salvation, my fortress, my strength.

13:45.991 --> 13:49.215
There is, as the series says, a way out.

13:50.076 --> 13:54.922
So I want us to talk about that because I think most of us are fearful in the same way about the same things.

13:56.244 --> 14:01.330
Psalm 27, one teaches us that first of all, our fear or my fear is uncertainty.

14:01.751 --> 14:04.114
I'm uncertain about the future.

14:04.994 --> 14:07.177
That fear, it's a fear of the future.

14:08.379 --> 14:12.224
Now my hope is that the Lord is my light, but we'll talk about that in a moment.

14:12.244 --> 14:16.610
I want us to talk about this sense of being uncertain and how it brings about fear.

14:18.513 --> 14:24.281
See, the reason everybody got quiet on the airplane is because they were uncertain of what the turbulence would do.

14:25.543 --> 14:30.610
Had they known it couldn't hurt the plane or that we were not going to crash, they would have continued to talk.

14:32.514 --> 14:34.336
We're fearful of cancer.

14:34.417 --> 14:36.920
Why because we're uncertain about what it's going to do.

14:37.000 --> 14:37.521
What's it mean?

14:37.621 --> 14:38.242
Am I dying?

14:39.904 --> 14:41.145
Am I going to have to have surgery?

14:41.366 --> 14:42.727
Am I going to have to have radiation?

14:42.988 --> 14:44.750
Am I going to have to have chemotherapy?

14:44.970 --> 14:46.232
I know what it did to my aunt.

14:46.312 --> 14:47.534
I know what happened to my mom.

14:47.594 --> 14:48.595
Is that going to happen to me?

14:48.976 --> 14:53.842
And not knowing what's going to happen being uncertain about the future creates what fear?

14:54.594 --> 14:58.420
Anxiety, worry, and it locks you out of your relationships.

14:58.520 --> 15:07.954
It locks you out of your dreams because you're uncertain about the future and because you don't know what's going to happen, you're waiting for whatever it is to happen, then you'll go back to life.

15:09.636 --> 15:09.997
Aging.

15:11.559 --> 15:13.102
Sometimes we're afraid of getting older, why?

15:13.122 --> 15:14.504
Because what's it gonna do?

15:16.226 --> 15:18.069
What diseases are gonna manifest itself?

15:19.992 --> 15:20.893
What's it gonna feel like?

15:20.993 --> 15:24.178
Are you gonna survive your spouse or your spouse gonna survive you?

15:26.498 --> 15:32.287
It can be frightening, bringing anxiety, worry, children, right?

15:32.908 --> 15:34.730
Did you know that children can be a monster?

15:34.750 --> 15:45.627
It can be quite frightening to realize that the first few years of your child's life, there's no greater influence than you.

15:46.868 --> 15:49.993
And the decisions you make will forever impact your kids' lives.

15:52.377 --> 15:53.198
Your mistakes?

15:55.061 --> 15:55.922
That can be scary.

15:57.602 --> 15:58.964
What if I screw up?

16:00.546 --> 16:00.967
I don't know.

16:01.668 --> 16:03.130
I don't know how it's going to impact them.

16:03.391 --> 16:05.534
I don't know how they're going to respond to my relationship.

16:05.554 --> 16:10.061
I don't know how they're going to respond to me losing my job or ending up in a divorce.

16:11.082 --> 16:11.723
I don't know.

16:11.764 --> 16:15.249
Marriage conflict can be the same way, right?

16:15.870 --> 16:17.913
You do know marriage can be a monster, I'm sure.

16:18.995 --> 16:21.298
And I'm not talking about the person sitting next to you.

16:22.530 --> 16:28.377
But I'm talking about the fact that once you find yourself in conflict, see conflict can breed intimacy if handled correctly.

16:28.698 --> 16:30.780
But often what it does is it makes us anxious.

16:30.861 --> 16:31.041
Why?

16:31.081 --> 16:33.624
Because your mom and dad used to fight before they ended up divorced.

16:35.166 --> 16:37.088
And now you and your spouse are doing the same thing.

16:39.171 --> 16:45.919
And the uncertainness or the uncertainty of the future, North Korea, what's going to happen there?

16:46.961 --> 16:47.922
Do we even know?

16:48.674 --> 16:49.416
the real thing.

16:49.436 --> 16:52.987
I mean, it's some dictator can push a button that would forever change the world.

16:55.375 --> 16:55.615
Is he?

16:57.320 --> 16:57.842
I don't know.

16:58.434 --> 16:59.035
politics.

16:59.435 --> 17:15.789
They tell us if you know this person believes this and this person believes this and if you vote for this person it's going to change the world like this and if this person wins it's going to make everything bad and all of those things but it's uncertain if we don't know what's actually going to happen or what they're actually going to do and that can make us anxious.

17:15.809 --> 17:16.670
You lose your job.

17:16.710 --> 17:17.310
What's that mean?

17:17.330 --> 17:18.271
Will you get another job?

17:18.491 --> 17:20.353
Will it pay as well as the job you have?

17:20.553 --> 17:22.014
Are you going to lose your insurance?

17:22.215 --> 17:25.337
How is your spouse going to respond to the fact that you lost your job?

17:25.357 --> 17:27.900
All those uncertainties bring fear and worry.

17:27.940 --> 17:28.420
We ask

17:28.400 --> 17:30.203
the question, what's going to happen?

17:30.263 --> 17:31.285
How bad will it be?

17:31.586 --> 17:32.768
Can I survive it?

17:33.349 --> 17:34.431
Am I going to be alone?

17:34.471 --> 17:41.845
This is the fear that I've always had this inability of not being certain, uncertainty.

17:41.885 --> 17:44.069
I remember when I was little, a mom and dad would go somewhere.

17:44.370 --> 17:48.658
If they didn't come home when they said they were going to come home, I got worried.

17:50.338 --> 17:53.062
And I didn't focus on all the good things that might be happening.

17:53.082 --> 17:55.825
They might be having a great time and staying out a little longer.

17:55.865 --> 18:00.191
They might have met somebody and building that friendship.

18:00.251 --> 18:02.634
No, I focused on the crash that they had.

18:04.096 --> 18:08.021
Now, I focused on the fight that they were experiencing, right?

18:08.041 --> 18:11.826
But because I was uncertain, this is the before cell phones.

18:12.962 --> 18:15.145
I was uncertain of where they were and what was going on.

18:15.186 --> 18:17.890
And even when Stefan and I got married, it was the same way.

18:17.950 --> 18:21.816
If she wasn't where she said she was gonna be, it'd be like, what's happened?

18:24.200 --> 18:26.443
Bring anxiety and worry and fear.

18:27.285 --> 18:28.847
We become anxious and afraid.

18:29.208 --> 18:30.470
And as a result, what do we do?

18:30.490 --> 18:31.832
We lock ourselves away.

18:31.892 --> 18:34.676
We hide behind the panic rooms.

18:34.736 --> 18:37.921
We hide behind our fear.

18:37.982 --> 18:40.786
Fear has a way of just causing us to freeze.

18:41.186 --> 18:42.594
But my hope is what?

18:42.654 --> 18:44.203
The Lord is light.

18:45.008 --> 18:45.792
And what does that mean?

18:46.053 --> 18:49.010
It means that the future is not dark to him.

18:49.890 --> 18:52.774
that God has always been and will always be.

18:52.814 --> 18:54.977
He is not confined by time.

18:55.398 --> 19:00.025
He knows my past, He knows my present, and He knows my future.

19:00.325 --> 19:01.907
He knows what's going on.

19:02.228 --> 19:04.351
Psalm 139 says it like this.

19:04.691 --> 19:06.734
You saw me, David is speaking to God.

19:06.814 --> 19:08.216
You saw me before I was born.

19:08.276 --> 19:09.037
That's the future.

19:09.418 --> 19:11.641
Every day of my life was recorded in your book.

19:11.801 --> 19:15.026
Every moment was laid out before a single day had passed.

19:15.330 --> 19:16.332
What is David saying?

19:16.352 --> 19:17.153
God, you know me.

19:17.253 --> 19:19.456
You know everything about me.

19:19.577 --> 19:21.459
You have a plan for me.

19:22.781 --> 19:27.569
Well, if God's got everything laid out, if there's a plan for me, my question is, well, what kind of plan is it?

19:27.769 --> 19:31.154
Because the doctors just told me, I've got this disease or this illness.

19:31.435 --> 19:33.859
I'm in the middle of this turbulence and is it going to lie?

19:33.879 --> 19:34.700
What's going to happen?

19:35.000 --> 19:36.162
What kind of plan is it?

19:36.202 --> 19:41.330
Well, Jeremiah 2911 says, I know the plans I have for you says the Lord.

19:41.698 --> 19:42.739
This is the same Lord.

19:42.779 --> 19:44.020
The Lord is my light.

19:44.401 --> 19:47.564
He has a plan for me and the plan that He has for me.

19:47.624 --> 19:48.285
What does it say?

19:48.585 --> 19:50.427
They are plans for what?

19:51.288 --> 19:51.548
What?

19:52.469 --> 19:55.952
They are plans for good and not for disaster.

19:55.992 --> 20:01.418
That's the plan that God has for me to give me a future and a hope.

20:03.259 --> 20:04.080
Well, that's good to know.

20:04.140 --> 20:05.622
It's great knowledge.

20:06.202 --> 20:09.906
God's got a plan, but you're still facing an uncertain future.

20:10.338 --> 20:13.262
We still don't know what the dictator in North Korea is going to do.

20:13.322 --> 20:16.667
We still don't know about all the division and disunity in our culture.

20:16.708 --> 20:18.070
What's going to be the impact of that?

20:18.090 --> 20:21.334
We still don't know how our spouse is going to respond to our lost job.

20:21.535 --> 20:26.021
How do we take this knowledge and actually experience it in our lives?

20:27.784 --> 20:29.046
Because that's the hard part, right?

20:30.108 --> 20:32.371
You can know something that you're not experiencing.

20:32.411 --> 20:39.762
You can know that God says He has a plan and it's a good plan and still be locked up in your panic room, scared to death of the future.

20:40.866 --> 20:46.414
I spent a year on this next passage of Scripture because I didn't want to just know something I wasn't experiencing.

20:47.575 --> 20:54.325
Philippians 4, verses 6, Paul says, don't worry and what is worry.

20:54.405 --> 20:57.670
It's just meditating on the bad things that can happen.

20:58.931 --> 21:03.077
It's meditating on, I don't know what the future holds, but whatever it is, it must be bad.

21:04.439 --> 21:06.482
He says, don't worry about what?

21:06.522 --> 21:07.203
What's the next word?

21:08.365 --> 21:09.426
Now, what is anything?

21:10.306 --> 21:15.212
It's anything, a dictator in North Korea.

21:15.593 --> 21:16.594
It's cancer.

21:16.795 --> 21:17.956
It's a lost job.

21:18.276 --> 21:19.438
It's getting older.

21:19.839 --> 21:20.680
It is anything.

21:20.760 --> 21:22.402
Don't worry about anything.

21:22.662 --> 21:24.304
Instead, pray about what?

21:25.326 --> 21:25.786
Everything.

21:26.647 --> 21:27.489
Don't worry about anything.

21:27.589 --> 21:29.171
Pray about everything.

21:29.211 --> 21:31.634
Tell God what you need, thinking for all that He has done.

21:31.842 --> 21:33.705
Verse seven, and this is the part.

21:33.765 --> 21:35.287
This is what I want for my life.

21:35.327 --> 21:42.356
It's what as your pastor, I want for your life, then you will, not might, not could, not if, then you will experience God's what?

21:43.238 --> 21:47.443
Peace, peace is the antithesis of worry and fear and anxiety, isn't it?

21:48.285 --> 21:49.887
That's what some of us are even here for.

21:49.927 --> 21:52.070
You happen to show up today because you want peace.

21:52.390 --> 21:58.098
You're torn out, overwhelmed, stressed out by worry and fear and anxiety.

21:58.818 --> 22:01.661
then you will experience God's peace, which succeeds anything you can understand.

22:01.941 --> 22:05.444
In other words, the world's not gonna understand, because they're gonna see the monster.

22:07.146 --> 22:08.948
They're gonna say, how can you have so much peace?

22:09.128 --> 22:10.890
You have this monster in your life.

22:12.851 --> 22:15.134
Don't you believe the medical report?

22:15.594 --> 22:16.475
It's a monster.

22:17.776 --> 22:19.158
Haven't you read the news?

22:19.258 --> 22:22.120
Haven't you heard the media of what could happen?

22:22.421 --> 22:24.623
What might take, how can you have peace?

22:26.645 --> 22:27.986
That's what God says is available.

22:29.666 --> 22:33.352
peace that passes understanding, peace that makes no sense.

22:33.592 --> 22:37.699
And it will, his peace will guard our hearts and minds as we live in Christ.

22:37.779 --> 22:41.224
I want that because there are a lot of monsters in my world.

22:43.588 --> 22:45.070
How do you embrace that?

22:45.090 --> 22:46.873
Well, I just wrote these three things down real quick.

22:47.194 --> 22:50.539
The first thing he says, don't worry about anything, but pray about everything.

22:50.579 --> 22:52.482
So in other words, share your fears.

22:53.744 --> 22:55.026
Share your fears.

22:55.746 --> 22:57.869
Go to God and say, God, I'm afraid of this.

22:57.949 --> 22:59.771
I'm afraid of what the doctors told me.

23:00.132 --> 23:01.794
I'm afraid of getting older.

23:01.934 --> 23:04.377
I'm afraid of what's going on in our world.

23:04.497 --> 23:06.420
I'm afraid of losing my job.

23:06.760 --> 23:08.643
I'm afraid of living in poverty.

23:08.743 --> 23:10.806
I'm afraid of not being able to retire.

23:11.366 --> 23:12.588
I am afraid.

23:13.089 --> 23:14.330
Share your fear.

23:14.471 --> 23:14.791
Why?

23:15.111 --> 23:20.178
Because if you don't share your fear, you're going to focus on what the monster?

23:21.410 --> 23:23.212
You're gonna meditate on the monster.

23:23.533 --> 23:27.398
Every day you're gonna get up and you're gonna think about what happens if you don't have enough to retire.

23:28.079 --> 23:28.900
Who's gonna take care of you?

23:30.802 --> 23:38.152
Every day you're gonna get up and you're gonna turn on the news and you're gonna see the newest report of what's going on somewhere in the world and it might happen to you next.

23:39.393 --> 23:49.266
But when you and I share when we begin to tell God our focus gets changed from the monster to God through prayer.

23:50.786 --> 23:59.262
So the first thing we have to do is we have to share our fears and worries and anxieties because whatever we hold on to is what we're going to focus on.

23:59.984 --> 24:03.390
And some of us are very focused on the monsters in our lives.

24:04.272 --> 24:11.506
In the very next verse, he says now, a very next phrase, tell God what you need and thanking for all that he's done.

24:11.842 --> 24:14.846
So we share our fear, but we focus on God's blessings.

24:15.126 --> 24:18.251
That's how we change or transfer our focus.

24:18.551 --> 24:20.333
We focus on blessing.

24:20.353 --> 24:22.096
What has God done in your life?

24:22.977 --> 24:25.380
The air that I breathe, He is provided.

24:25.660 --> 24:28.044
The life that I have, He has given me.

24:28.104 --> 24:32.870
I'm focusing that He is the alpha and the omega, the beginning and the end.

24:33.130 --> 24:35.874
He's all powerful, all knowing everywhere at one time.

24:36.174 --> 24:38.157
And I'm no longer focused on the monster.

24:38.277 --> 24:41.842
I'm focused on God's blessings in the past and therefore.

24:42.146 --> 24:45.252
The third thing is then I expect God's peace in the future.

24:46.435 --> 24:47.857
I'm not hoping for God's peace.

24:47.878 --> 24:49.360
I'm not wishing for God's peace.

24:49.421 --> 24:50.423
I'm expecting it.

24:52.427 --> 25:00.082
I don't care who the monster is or how ugly or boo scary he is or she is.

25:01.570 --> 25:03.653
My focus is not on the size of the monster.

25:03.733 --> 25:05.716
My focus is on God's blessing.

25:05.736 --> 25:08.400
Therefore, I am expecting God's peace.

25:08.761 --> 25:10.023
See, you don't have to be afraid.

25:10.043 --> 25:16.753
You don't have to lock yourself behind some panic room doors because the Lord is our light.

25:18.195 --> 25:19.657
And he sees into all darkness.

25:20.698 --> 25:25.225
The second fear that I think we have is, well, my fear is guilt.

25:26.187 --> 25:27.689
Where does my light and my salvation?

25:27.989 --> 25:31.154
Now, fear of uncertainty is

25:31.842 --> 25:33.964
the future, this is the past.

25:35.166 --> 25:36.888
This is when we're fearful of the past.

25:36.908 --> 25:38.790
Now our hope is that God is salvation.

25:39.030 --> 25:41.893
But let's talk about this thing called guilt.

25:41.913 --> 25:47.260
See, guilt fear is when the monster shows up in our lives, you know what we begin to think?

25:48.040 --> 25:49.082
I knew you were coming.

25:51.464 --> 25:53.006
Because I've done some things I shouldn't have done.

25:54.368 --> 25:55.869
And I knew when I did them, they were wrong.

25:57.972 --> 25:59.954
There's some things in my life I haven't done.

26:00.930 --> 26:02.232
I knew I needed to help.

26:03.153 --> 26:06.097
I felt God nudge my heart, but I just didn't do it because I didn't want to.

26:06.838 --> 26:08.020
I didn't think I had the time.

26:08.160 --> 26:09.783
I rationalized and convinced myself.

26:10.784 --> 26:14.710
I knew, I knew it'd show up.

26:14.730 --> 26:15.691
It's just my punishment.

26:17.413 --> 26:18.375
It's just what happens.

26:19.697 --> 26:23.242
It's just God reminding me that He's in control.

26:23.302 --> 26:29.010
In other words, it's God that sent the monster to discipline me, punish me.

26:29.954 --> 26:31.036
the things that I've done.

26:31.076 --> 26:36.024
Now that all sounds fine and dandy, but that's not what the Scripture teaches.

26:36.885 --> 26:41.753
And John chapter 3 and verse 17, it says, God sent his son into the world.

26:41.973 --> 26:45.299
So we're going to find out why Jesus came, not to judge the world.

26:45.339 --> 26:47.462
Now you can change the word world to you.

26:47.502 --> 26:48.664
You are part of the world.

26:49.666 --> 26:52.370
So God sent his son not to judge you.

26:52.482 --> 26:53.784
Not to point his fingers at us.

26:53.804 --> 26:54.846
I saw what you did last night.

26:54.906 --> 26:55.687
I know where you were.

26:55.707 --> 26:56.829
I know what you've said.

26:56.889 --> 26:57.650
I know where you've been.

26:57.670 --> 26:58.711
I know how you've acted.

26:58.771 --> 26:59.833
I know what you haven't done.

26:59.873 --> 27:02.377
And I know the gifts that you have and what you could have done.

27:03.158 --> 27:04.039
That's not why I came.

27:04.300 --> 27:06.403
I didn't come to judge the world, but to what?

27:07.024 --> 27:07.445
Save.

27:08.266 --> 27:12.813
Rescue the world through him.

27:13.614 --> 27:16.979
Now, there is one who accuses, right?

27:17.219 --> 27:18.581
Whispers in your ear all the time.

27:19.102 --> 27:20.684
You deserve what you're getting.

27:20.704 --> 27:21.746
You ought to lose your job.

27:23.042 --> 27:25.545
You ought to lose your spouse after what you've done.

27:25.585 --> 27:26.767
Look, look how you've hurt her.

27:26.987 --> 27:28.149
Look how you've hurt your kids.

27:28.169 --> 27:29.150
Look how you've hurt him.

27:29.471 --> 27:31.053
Look what you've done to that business.

27:31.073 --> 27:32.475
Look, you deserve it.

27:32.895 --> 27:35.839
There is an accuser of the brethren is what the Scripture says.

27:38.062 --> 27:39.644
But he's called the enemy.

27:39.705 --> 27:43.730
The Bible says Satan is our adversary.

27:44.386 --> 27:55.708
The one who came to steal, kill, and destroy that whispers into our ear that the monster we're experiencing, the disease that we've been diagnosed with is a result of something that we have done in the past.

27:55.728 --> 27:57.150
But that's not what God says.

27:57.211 --> 27:59.655
God says, I didn't come to get even with you.

27:59.936 --> 28:03.943
I came to rescue you from whatever monster you're experiencing in your life.

28:05.226 --> 28:07.410
That's why you don't have to be afraid.

28:07.746 --> 28:13.794
Psalm 46 says it, God is our refuge and strength, always circle that, always, always what?

28:14.015 --> 28:16.306
Ready to help in times of trouble.

28:16.770 --> 28:23.198
It doesn't say sometimes, it doesn't say if you've done all the right things, if you've never been bad, if you've never screwed up.

28:23.218 --> 28:24.380
That's not what it says.

28:24.660 --> 28:30.308
It says, when the monster shows up in your life, you better know somebody else is showing up at the very same team.

28:30.548 --> 28:36.776
God is there, and the reason God is there is not to say, I told you so, or to watch you get your rear-end kick.

28:36.816 --> 28:44.146
No, the reason God shows up is because he will always be there to rescue you and I in times of trouble.

28:47.330 --> 28:49.614
So we don't have to run to the panic room.

28:50.094 --> 29:00.391
We don't have to lock ourselves away from our relationships and our future and our dreams and our hopes because of something that we've done or experienced in our past.

29:00.411 --> 29:01.673
Go, how do you deal with your past?

29:02.874 --> 29:04.918
How do you keep it from haunting your future?

29:04.998 --> 29:15.314
Well, and first John 1 9, it says, but if we confess our sins, remember the word sin picture word, it means to miss the perfection, to miss the bull's eye, which is perfection.

29:16.194 --> 29:22.080
So we've all done it, but if we confess that we've screwed up, that we've missed the bullseye, he is faithful and just to do what?

29:22.120 --> 29:22.541
Get even?

29:23.141 --> 29:23.822
Get revenge?

29:24.483 --> 29:25.264
Send a monster?

29:25.324 --> 29:27.026
Make you afraid?

29:27.126 --> 29:28.287
No, that's not what it says.

29:28.567 --> 29:30.049
He's faithful and just to what?

29:31.250 --> 29:31.711
Forgive.

29:32.872 --> 29:33.893
To forgive if our sins.

29:33.913 --> 29:34.954
What's the word forgive me?

29:35.515 --> 29:39.039
It means to separate you and I from our sin as far as the east is from the west.

29:39.419 --> 29:43.984
It means that although our sins be a scarlet, they'll be made as white as snow.

29:44.985 --> 29:45.906
To take away.

29:46.082 --> 29:50.569
cleanse, make anew from all of our wickedness.

29:50.869 --> 29:56.899
See, my hope, the Lord is my light and my salvation.

29:57.359 --> 29:58.401
He's my rescuer.

29:58.661 --> 30:00.043
He is my forgiver.

30:00.464 --> 30:01.626
So I don't have to be afraid.

30:02.447 --> 30:03.729
And I don't have to be anxious.

30:03.949 --> 30:08.536
And I don't have to be looking over my shoulder, wondering when the monster is going to show up in my life.

30:08.837 --> 30:14.866
Because even should he show up, God is my refuge, my forgiver, my hope.

30:14.978 --> 30:16.400
and my salvation.

30:18.002 --> 30:18.463
Last one.

30:20.105 --> 30:24.011
So we think about uncertainty, fear of the future.

30:24.111 --> 30:26.033
We think about our guilt.

30:26.814 --> 30:29.098
We have this past catching up with us.

30:30.479 --> 30:35.226
The third fear is inadequacy, which is the fear of the present, right?

30:35.346 --> 30:35.887
The monster.

30:35.947 --> 30:38.370
It's here right now.

30:40.213 --> 30:41.795
I mean, you just got the diagnosis.

30:42.276 --> 30:43.858
You watched the news before you came.

30:45.922 --> 30:53.069
It's all what's going on there in North Korea, division in other parts of our country, people saying this, doing that.

30:54.631 --> 30:55.892
I mean, it's right here right now.

30:55.932 --> 30:57.554
You lost your job just this week.

30:58.755 --> 31:04.501
Your children made some bad decisions just this week, and you're wondering if there's anything to do with the bad decisions you've made in your life.

31:04.541 --> 31:05.902
I mean, it's right here.

31:06.403 --> 31:10.647
It is the president, and it is the sense that we feel inadequate to deal with it.

31:12.349 --> 31:13.490
It feels overwhelming.

31:14.882 --> 31:15.162
Right?

31:15.202 --> 31:16.745
We're not strong enough.

31:16.845 --> 31:19.549
Now, the hope is that the Lord is my strength.

31:19.569 --> 31:20.910
But let's talk about this fear.

31:21.031 --> 31:25.737
I'm not strong enough to overcome the scary thing that's in front of me right now.

31:26.038 --> 31:28.601
And whether it be cancer, it's stronger than you.

31:28.942 --> 31:30.484
You can eat all the right foods.

31:30.524 --> 31:32.286
You can do all the procedures.

31:32.346 --> 31:35.951
And yet you and I both know of people who have done those things and not survived.

31:36.012 --> 31:36.933
It's stronger than you.

31:39.156 --> 31:40.658
The addiction's stronger than you.

31:41.026 --> 31:48.799
You've said how many times that you would never do that again only to find yourself doing it once again, even though you know it hurts the people that you love the most.

31:49.841 --> 31:51.183
Poverty is stronger than you.

31:51.243 --> 31:53.246
You're in the fourth generation.

31:53.327 --> 31:54.829
Your mom and dad didn't have anything.

31:54.889 --> 31:56.271
Your grandparents didn't have anything.

31:56.492 --> 31:58.375
Your great grandparents didn't have anything.

31:58.695 --> 32:01.701
And you struggle with the fear of poverty.

32:02.642 --> 32:05.146
It's stronger than you, turbulent, stronger than you, right?

32:05.206 --> 32:06.348
I can't hold that airplane up.

32:06.408 --> 32:07.410
I'm not Superman.

32:08.834 --> 32:12.379
North Korea, if he pushes the button, there's nothing I can do to stop him from doing that.

32:13.240 --> 32:15.904
I can't shoot down the rockets.

32:15.924 --> 32:17.266
There's nothing I can do.

32:18.448 --> 32:18.968
Failure.

32:20.050 --> 32:20.891
Fear of failure.

32:21.212 --> 32:23.395
All of these things are stronger than me.

32:23.855 --> 32:27.761
I told you earlier that I had the opportunity to go and spend some time with my dad.

32:27.801 --> 32:31.807
And, you know, my dad's always been strong.

32:32.548 --> 32:36.914
I remember when I was a kid, my dad dropped a manhole cover on his feet.

32:37.154 --> 32:38.716
It broke both of his big toes.

32:39.517 --> 32:45.245
Well, the next day he cut the toes of his shoes out and he went to work.

32:46.286 --> 32:47.668
My dad pulled his tooth.

32:47.708 --> 32:51.333
He had a cavity with a pair of pliers.

32:53.376 --> 32:57.862
When my dad had quadruple bypass surgery, he was up the very same day.

32:57.902 --> 32:59.745
He never said he'd never hurt.

33:00.866 --> 33:03.730
He never had a headache.

33:04.066 --> 33:08.915
Now with, and he'd had his tongue operated on in the past and he had done fine with that.

33:08.935 --> 33:10.759
I'd never seen my dad fearfully.

33:10.779 --> 33:11.741
It always been strong.

33:12.262 --> 33:15.668
It always responded to whatever obstacle was in front of him.

33:17.352 --> 33:19.937
But this is stronger than him.

33:21.540 --> 33:26.108
Before the last, the first serger asked him, well, how long do you think it'd be in the hospital?

33:26.128 --> 33:26.930
Oh, a couple of days.

33:29.058 --> 33:32.943
And he got out and then he was back in and this didn't work right.

33:32.963 --> 33:37.870
And I've never seen my dad give up because this is stronger than him.

33:39.653 --> 33:41.375
He's never felt weak.

33:41.395 --> 33:42.957
He's always been strong enough.

33:43.258 --> 33:44.259
But here's the truth.

33:45.701 --> 33:54.153
All of us at one time or another, some of us many times will face things that are stronger than us.

33:54.173 --> 33:54.794
They're stronger.

33:55.054 --> 33:57.778
Listen, it doesn't matter how much money you got in the bank.

33:58.402 --> 34:00.984
Doesn't matter how great your insurance is.

34:02.126 --> 34:04.768
Doesn't matter how solid your job is.

34:04.788 --> 34:07.731
The Scripture says all those things can be gone and you know they can't be.

34:07.751 --> 34:12.215
That's why you keep putting money in the bank and you keep buying insurance.

34:12.235 --> 34:13.116
It's your panic room.

34:14.137 --> 34:14.677
It's your hope.

34:16.659 --> 34:17.440
It's your peace.

34:17.480 --> 34:26.488
The only problem is it doesn't bring greater, great peace because you know it's not enough and you know should a dictator push the button, no bank account, no insurance.

34:26.508 --> 34:28.210
None of that's going to protect you.

34:29.666 --> 34:33.814
Did you find yourself in the wrong place when a terrorist decides to do something?

34:36.619 --> 34:39.204
And it is that fear, again, that locks us up.

34:39.224 --> 34:40.426
But what does the Scripture say?

34:40.807 --> 34:43.111
Isaiah 41, 10 says, don't be afraid.

34:43.933 --> 34:46.718
Now, I don't know about you, but when I read something like that, here's what I ask.

34:46.818 --> 34:47.219
Why?

34:49.042 --> 34:49.243
Right?

34:49.443 --> 34:50.445
I mean, it's easy to say it.

34:50.465 --> 34:51.066
Don't be afraid.

34:51.106 --> 34:52.268
We've been told that our whole life.

34:52.308 --> 34:53.170
Don't be afraid.

34:53.346 --> 34:54.447
Don't be afraid of the dark.

34:54.467 --> 34:55.808
Don't be afraid of what's under your bed.

34:55.848 --> 34:57.349
Don't be afraid of what's in the closet.

34:57.530 --> 34:58.631
Don't be afraid of that clown.

34:58.811 --> 35:00.012
Don't be afraid of Santa Claus.

35:00.292 --> 35:00.973
Don't be afraid.

35:01.033 --> 35:01.533
Well, why?

35:01.733 --> 35:03.415
Why shouldn't I be afraid?

35:04.055 --> 35:06.918
Well, the Scripture tells us, for I am with you.

35:06.978 --> 35:08.439
Well, who is I am?

35:09.080 --> 35:11.322
I am the Alpha and the Omega.

35:11.522 --> 35:13.363
I am the beginning and the end.

35:13.784 --> 35:15.385
I am the all-powerful.

35:15.585 --> 35:16.746
I am the all-knowing.

35:17.087 --> 35:19.088
I am the everywhere-at-one-time God.

35:19.469 --> 35:21.731
I am the one who created life.

35:21.911 --> 35:23.332
I am the one who breathed

35:23.312 --> 35:24.453
into your nostrils.

35:24.493 --> 35:27.616
When Moses asks the question, who should I say is sending me?

35:27.676 --> 35:28.377
What did he say?

35:28.697 --> 35:30.219
Tell them I am.

35:30.259 --> 35:34.143
And I am was not only with Moses, he's with you and I.

35:34.163 --> 35:38.167
Don't be afraid, he says.

35:38.227 --> 35:39.989
I am with you.

35:40.049 --> 35:41.330
Do not be discouraged.

35:41.390 --> 35:42.892
Again, I ask the question, why?

35:42.932 --> 35:49.979
Because the monster is big and it is discouraging to know that that monster is in my life.

35:49.999 --> 35:51.501
Why should I not be discouraged?

35:51.541 --> 35:52.882
For I am.

35:53.282 --> 35:55.747
Not only with you, I am your God.

35:55.767 --> 35:58.533
I will strengthen you and help you.

35:58.553 --> 36:02.380
I will hold you up in my victorious right hand.

36:02.601 --> 36:07.771
Now here's what I would encourage you to do is go through there and circle all the words I. I am your God.

36:07.992 --> 36:08.493
I will.

36:08.954 --> 36:09.695
I will hold you.

36:09.715 --> 36:12.561
Listen, God doesn't delegate to the angels.

36:14.465 --> 36:15.186
Your fear.

36:16.994 --> 36:20.639
I love the fact that God doesn't say, you know, Troy seems to be scared about that.

36:20.940 --> 36:23.684
Michael or some angel, you know, we've never heard of.

36:24.245 --> 36:25.767
Go, go down there and help him.

36:28.111 --> 36:30.574
God doesn't delegate you or me to the angels.

36:30.594 --> 36:31.776
What does that scripture say?

36:32.257 --> 36:40.329
God, the I am, the all-powerful God takes his hand and he holds me up and he strengthens me.

36:40.889 --> 36:43.954
I have the attention of God.

36:46.722 --> 36:51.368
So I may be weak, but he is strong.

36:51.408 --> 36:52.230
Isn't that what Paul said?

36:53.391 --> 37:00.221
See, my dad knew how to deal with strength, but he never learned how to deal with weakness.

37:02.704 --> 37:03.545
It's easy to do.

37:03.585 --> 37:06.029
It's easy to spend your whole life.

37:06.049 --> 37:08.532
Now we say, I'm trusting God.

37:11.036 --> 37:12.598
But where's your panic room?

37:12.618 --> 37:13.940
Where do you run when you're afraid?

37:13.960 --> 37:15.602
Do you run to your bank account?

37:17.762 --> 37:19.526
Or do you run to what you stored in heaven?

37:20.608 --> 37:21.910
Do you run to your insurance?

37:22.231 --> 37:23.614
Or do you run to the great physician?

37:23.694 --> 37:25.177
I'm not saying those things are bad.

37:25.598 --> 37:28.704
Need to be wise, but I'm asking you, where do you run?

37:30.047 --> 37:30.989
Now, what do you say?

37:31.049 --> 37:33.253
Where do you run?

37:33.454 --> 37:37.401
There's a great example of it in Second Chronicles.

37:37.862 --> 37:39.666
King Jehosephat was

37:39.874 --> 37:41.596
a good king of God's people.

37:41.636 --> 37:45.020
They had some bad kings who didn't follow God, and then they had some who did follow God.

37:45.380 --> 37:48.443
This is a, he was young, but he's a good king.

37:48.464 --> 37:49.244
He followed God.

37:49.925 --> 37:51.006
But look at what happens.

37:51.026 --> 37:52.668
Some people came to see him some one day.

37:52.688 --> 37:54.350
It's not in your outline, but it's up on the screen.

37:54.650 --> 37:57.293
Second Chronicles chapter 20, verses two and three.

37:57.574 --> 38:00.056
Says, messengers came and they told Jehoshaphat.

38:01.238 --> 38:08.786
A vast army, big army from Edom is marching against you from beyond the Dead Sea.

38:09.122 --> 38:14.412
Not only is there a big army coming, they are already at Azizuzan.

38:17.177 --> 38:20.042
Tamar, I apologize, all right.

38:20.062 --> 38:20.543
What's he saying?

38:20.563 --> 38:22.327
He's saying they're almost here.

38:22.367 --> 38:26.655
They're already at this place.

38:26.675 --> 38:28.759
Jehoshaphat was, what's it say?

38:30.001 --> 38:30.482
Terrified.

38:30.983 --> 38:32.626
You ever got news that terrified you?

38:33.922 --> 38:36.286
You ever had somebody tell you something that terrified you?

38:36.306 --> 38:41.816
You ever got a doctor's report or turned on and saw a report on the news or something that terrified you?

38:42.277 --> 38:45.883
It was terrified by the news and he begged the Lord for guidance.

38:46.004 --> 38:47.546
I like where he ran though, don't you?

38:49.390 --> 38:53.537
He didn't run to his army and say, hey, do we have enough troops?

38:53.677 --> 38:56.402
Do we need to, you know, do we need to draft a few people?

38:56.482 --> 39:01.028
He didn't run to his military generals and say, hey, do we have the newest weapons?

39:01.088 --> 39:02.650
Do we have the newest technology?

39:02.931 --> 39:04.012
The Scripture says no.

39:04.373 --> 39:06.956
He went to God and he begged God.

39:07.216 --> 39:08.178
What did he beg God for?

39:08.238 --> 39:09.700
What's it say?

39:09.720 --> 39:10.221
Guidance.

39:10.301 --> 39:11.202
That's interesting, isn't it?

39:11.662 --> 39:13.585
He didn't beg God to take away the enemy.

39:15.167 --> 39:15.327
Right?

39:15.367 --> 39:16.209
We tend to do that.

39:16.309 --> 39:23.218
No, he begged God for guidance and then he asked the people or ordered the people of Judah to fast.

39:23.330 --> 39:31.881
See, you and I sometimes want God to take away the monster, where what God wants to do is show His power in the monster.

39:32.402 --> 39:37.889
See, the scripture says, all things work together for good for those who love the Lord and are called according to His purpose.

39:37.909 --> 39:41.414
And so the enemy sends this monster to scare you.

39:42.315 --> 39:44.658
And it's scary.

39:45.154 --> 39:52.705
And it's big and everything inside of you and I wants to run because the enemy wants to use it to destroy you.

39:52.965 --> 40:03.380
But God says, I'm going to take the very thing that the enemy is brought into your life and I'm going to turn it on its head because I'm going to use that fear to strengthen you.

40:03.721 --> 40:12.914
I'm going to use that fear for you to see that I truly am the all powerful God and that you never have to be afraid.

40:13.826 --> 40:17.450
If Jehoshaphat prayed, God, give me some wisdom.

40:18.491 --> 40:20.354
I don't know what to do, and I'm scared.

40:21.815 --> 40:23.217
Well, what was God's response?

40:25.199 --> 40:26.681
Verse 15, same chapter.

40:27.282 --> 40:30.726
He said, listen to all the people of Judah and Jerusalem.

40:31.447 --> 40:33.229
Even you, King Jehoshaphat, listen.

40:33.909 --> 40:36.072
This is what the Lord says, do not be afraid.

40:36.152 --> 40:37.133
Okay, there we go again.

40:37.233 --> 40:37.874
Why?

40:38.914 --> 40:41.320
Don't be discouraged by this mighty armor.

40:41.340 --> 40:42.784
Here's what I love about the Bible.

40:42.984 --> 40:45.491
The Bible doesn't discount the size of the monster.

40:46.634 --> 40:48.157
You notice that?

40:48.177 --> 40:48.759
What does it say?

40:48.839 --> 40:50.002
It's a vast army.

40:51.522 --> 40:53.124
He says, don't be discouraged.

40:53.184 --> 40:54.206
It's a big army, man.

40:54.246 --> 40:55.428
They've got technology.

40:55.448 --> 40:56.309
They've got giants.

40:56.329 --> 40:57.791
This is a big army.

40:57.831 --> 41:03.900
It's a lot of people with a lot of weapons, and they are marching, and you can hear the thunder of their feet as it hits the ground.

41:04.200 --> 41:08.146
But even though the army is big and powerful, you don't have to be afraid.

41:08.206 --> 41:08.486
Why?

41:08.686 --> 41:10.148
Because it's not your battle.

41:10.409 --> 41:12.572
It's God's.

41:12.592 --> 41:16.978
And while that army may be big, it is not bigger than your God.

41:17.378 --> 41:34.005
And it is one of the great benefits of being a Christ follower, is that there are monsters in my life and in your life, and there are big monsters, and they are scary monsters, and they are even powerful monsters, and they have taken out people in the past, but that monster is not bigger than my God.

41:34.265 --> 41:37.330
And it is his battle, he says, it is not my battle.

41:40.802 --> 41:46.709
It's not going to be taken on by my bank account or by my insurance or by my skill or by my mind.

41:47.090 --> 41:49.032
It's going to be taken on by his.

41:49.472 --> 41:51.635
So I will not be afraid.

41:53.177 --> 41:54.739
I will not be anxious.

41:54.899 --> 42:05.431
I will not run and lock myself in from the people and the dreams and the purpose of my life because the battle is not mine.

42:07.314 --> 42:07.634
Now,

42:09.314 --> 42:12.158
You can focus on the mask or the monster.

42:13.499 --> 42:15.442
You can be uncertain about the future.

42:15.542 --> 42:20.828
You can be overwhelmed by your guilt or what you've done in the past.

42:20.849 --> 42:23.752
You can feel overwhelmed and inadequate.

42:24.673 --> 42:28.018
Or you can be reminded that the Lord is your light.

42:30.140 --> 42:31.222
There is no darkness.

42:32.743 --> 42:34.666
You can be reminded he is your salvation.

42:36.068 --> 42:37.970
He has taken all of that away.

42:38.210 --> 42:41.334
and that He is your fortress and He is your strength.

42:42.335 --> 42:44.938
The battle is not yours, but it is His.

42:46.740 --> 42:47.941
But we all have to decide that.

42:47.982 --> 42:53.588
The way we wanted to end today is a little bit different.

42:53.608 --> 43:01.858
You probably saw when you came in all of our campuses, we have those locks, they're little locks, but they're on the cross.

43:03.580 --> 43:05.362
And they all represent something.

43:05.474 --> 43:08.997
They represent our fear, because that's what fear does, anxiety, worry.

43:09.978 --> 43:13.542
It locks us in, makes us afraid to move forward.

43:15.223 --> 43:15.964
And we all have them.

43:16.945 --> 43:17.866
I don't know what yours is.

43:18.747 --> 43:20.348
Maybe I've mentioned it, maybe I have it.

43:21.729 --> 43:29.857
But you know, and I want you to think about that for a moment, because that's what this little lock symbolizes.

43:29.877 --> 43:34.962
In a moment, I'm going to give you an opportunity to do something about that is

43:36.770 --> 43:37.992
we have these little keys.

43:39.976 --> 43:46.468
Not very big, but the interesting thing about these keys is they fit into the lock and they open it.

43:48.071 --> 43:55.685
And we wanted to give you a way to act, to symbolize, to be reminded that you don't have to be fearful.

43:57.368 --> 44:00.594
And so I'm going to pray for us and we're going to sing

44:01.090 --> 44:02.272
worship the last song.

44:02.552 --> 44:07.460
And as we do, I'm going to invite you to leave your seat and to go to one of these crosses.

44:07.480 --> 44:08.401
We have them here at the floor.

44:08.462 --> 44:09.764
They're up there in the balcony.

44:10.845 --> 44:11.947
And they're going to give you a key.

44:11.987 --> 44:16.714
And then take the key, just unlock one of these locks.

44:17.396 --> 44:21.442
Symbolicly thinking, this is this sphere in my life.

44:21.502 --> 44:22.403
This is my anxiety.

44:22.423 --> 44:23.245
This is my worry.

44:23.645 --> 44:24.186
Unlock it.

44:24.246 --> 44:25.889
And then there are big baskets there.

44:25.909 --> 44:27.411
So just kind of throw it in the basket.

44:28.212 --> 44:29.234
But take the key with you.

44:30.242 --> 44:35.788
as a reminder that you don't have to be afraid.

44:38.411 --> 44:41.014
Like the series says, there is a way out.

44:42.436 --> 44:45.619
It's our light, our salvation, and our strength.

44:46.760 --> 44:47.501
Would you bow your head?

44:50.304 --> 44:58.994
Father, I pray that we would be set free from our

44:59.810 --> 45:04.735
panic rooms and our fear and our worry and our anxiety.

45:10.402 --> 45:11.984
Thank you that we don't have to be afraid.

45:13.525 --> 45:28.562
May these next few moments, may we have a sticky mind, may we act in faith, breaking free in Jesus' name.

45:29.218 --> 45:30.028
Let's stand.

45:30.900 --> 45:31.730
Let's respond.

